<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Ajaycent Angles and the person behind it."
	pubDate={new Date('July 17 2026')}
>
	<p>
		Ajaycent Angles is written by Ajay Phatak. It covers tech, finance, politics, and philosophy —
		with a particular interest in the connections between them. The name is a pun on "adjacent
		angles": in geometry, two angles that share a common side. Most of what gets written here lives
		on those shared sides.
	</p>

	<p>
		Alongside the essays, this site hosts live data projects, starting with the
		<a href="https://elections.ajaycent.com">2026 Election Tracker</a> — a dashboard following
		Senate and House races through the 2026 midterms.
	</p>

	<p>
		Questions, corrections, or disagreements are welcome:
		<a href="mailto:wizard944@gmail.com">wizard944@gmail.com</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
